<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1373,1974]" pageId="12" pageNumber="485">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,1913,1938]" pageId="12" pageNumber="485">Notes.</emphasis>
This species closely resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baker" authorityYear="1914" box="[626,767,1913,1937]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Makilingia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="485" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis box="[626,767,1913,1937]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="485">M. maculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in size and color pattern but differs in having the head more strongly produced and in the structure of the male genitalia.
</paragraph>
